title: Wrong suggestion for `explicit_outlives_requirements` in macro

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Steps to reproduce ```sh git clone https://github.com/serde-rs/serde cd serde git switch --detach v1.0.151 RUSTFLAGS=-Wexplicit-outlives-requirements cargo +stage1 check ``` ### Meta master at 2d8651a92761421b0437ffb44ba5670bea5ee1df config.toml: ```toml profile = "compiler" changelog-seen = 2 [rust] debuginfo-level = 1 # show line numbers debug = true [llvm] assertions = true ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Span must not be empty and have no suggestion', /home/lukas/code/rust/compiler/rustc_errors/src/diagnostic.rs:633:9 ```
